&nbsp;Eric Bana has signed on to replace Vince Vaughn as a serial killer seeking redemption in &#8220;The Forgiven.&#8221;In the film adaptation of Michael Ashton&#8217;s play &#8220;The Archbishop and the Antichrist,&#8221; Bana will star opposite Forest Whitaker, who plays Archbishop Desmond Tutu, reports Deadline.The drama follows a fictionalized account of Tutu&#8217;s meetings with murderer Piet Blomfield, who is seeking redemption for his crimes while serving a life sentence in prison in post-apartheid South Africa.Directing is Roland Joff , who also co-wrote the screenplay with Ashton.-Relaxnews